 great effort, asked him, “How long ago did you leave Russia?”

“Five years,” he answered curtly; and then, as he sat in a corner in the languorous violet light which poured over the cloth on the table in the center of the room and over the smiling faces of Kolin and Gornotsvetov, who were dancing silently and energetically in the middle of the room, Ganin thought, “What happiness! Tomorrow—no, it’s today, it’s already past midnight. Mary cannot have changed since then, her Tarta